body:
Hey I&#039;m relatively new to LOL and I&#039;m thinking that it would be great for more variety of maps available in normal mode like minion lanes intersecting at points for great ambushes and high areas where terrain is important for decisive battles e.g. a cliff where some brush hides a player, uses flash to jump on an enemy while chasing another player, etc. {{summoner:4}} 

Maybe including some bridges that overlap lanes for interesting combat, having a turret on a pedestal near said bridge requiring you to get to the bridge to attack in melee (not ranged or will be too hard) and melee minions will behave differently. Melee could circle to the turret and may fight the enemy melee minions unless a champion kills them before them to allow more damage to the turret (Players would be inclined to protect the minions more in this instance) Maybe have 2 bridges in mirror fashion 

Other creative ideas on this discussion will be appreciated :)

{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}} {{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}
